.Dd March 28, 2026
.Dt GALE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm gale
.Nd isolated package management for developers
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar command
.Op Ar args ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
installs packages into versioned, isolated directories.
Each version has its own store path.
Projects pin dependencies in
.Pa gale.toml ;
a lockfile records SHA256 hashes.
Prebuilt binaries are preferred; source builds are
the fallback.
.Sh COMMANDS
.Ss Package Management
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm install Ar pkg Ns Op @ Ns Ar ver
Install a package.
.It Cm remove Ar pkg
Remove a package.
.It Cm add Ar pkg Ns Op @ Ns Ar ver ...
Add to
.Pa gale.toml
without installing.
.It Cm sync
Install packages at pinned versions.
.It Cm update Op Ar pkg Ns Op @ Ns Ar ver ...
Update to latest or specified version.
.It Cm list
List packages in
.Pa gale.toml .
.It Cm gc
Remove unused versions from the store.
.El
.Ss Inspection
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm which Ar binary
Show which package provides a binary.
.It Cm outdated
Show packages with newer versions.
.It Cm diff
Show what
.Cm sync
would change.
.It Cm doctor
Check for problems.
.It Cm search Ar query
Search by name or description.
.El
.Ss Project Environment
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm env
Print
.Ev PATH
export.
.It Cm init
Create
.Pa gale.toml
and
.Pa .envrc .
.It Cm shell
Open a shell with the project environment.
.It Cm run Ar cmd
Run a command in the project environment.
.It Cm hook direnv
Print
.Fn use_gale
for direnvrc.
.El
.Ss Recipe Development
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm build Ar recipe.toml
Build from source.
.It Cm lint Ar recipe.toml ...
Validate recipe files.
.It Cm create-recipe Ar repo
Generate a recipe from a GitHub repo using AI.
Accepts
.Ar owner/repo
or a full URL.
Requires an Anthropic API key in
.Pa ~/.gale/config.toml .
.It Cm import homebrew Ar name
Import a Homebrew formula.
.El
.Sh FLAGS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -local
Resolve recipes from sibling
.Pa gale-recipes .
.It Fl -source Ar dir
Build from a local source directory.
.It Fl -git
Build from git HEAD.
.It Fl -recipe Ar file
Use a specific recipe file.
.It Fl g , -global
Write to global config.
.It Fl p , -project
Write to project config.
.It Fl -no-color
Disable colored output.
.El
.Sh BUILD ENVIRONMENT
Build steps run in a clean shell with these variables:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "DYLD_FALLBACK_LIBRARY_PATH" -compact
.It Ev PREFIX
Install destination.
.It Ev VERSION
Package version from the recipe.
.It Ev JOBS
CPU count.
.It Ev OS
Operating system.
.It Ev ARCH
Architecture.
.It Ev PLATFORM
.Ev OS Ns - Ns Ev ARCH .
.It Ev LIBRARY_PATH
Library directories from dependencies.
.It Ev C_INCLUDE_PATH
Header directories from dependencies.
.It Ev PKG_CONFIG_PATH
Pkg-config directories from dependencies.
.It Ev LD_LIBRARY_PATH
Dynamic linker path (Linux).
.It Ev DYLD_FALLBACK_LIBRARY_PATH
Dynamic linker fallback path (macOS).
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Install a package:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale install jq
.Ed
.Pp
Pin a specific version:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale install jq@1.7.1
.Ed
.Pp
Set up a project:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale init
$ echo 'go = "1.26.1"' >> gale.toml
$ gale sync
.Ed
.Pp
Check what needs updating:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale outdated
jq 1.7.1 \(-> 1.8.1
.Ed
.Pp
Build a recipe from source:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale build recipes/j/jq.toml
.Ed
.Pp
Find which package provides a binary:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
$ gale which jq
jq@1.8.1
/Users/you/.gale/pkg/jq/1.8.1/bin/jq
.Ed
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ev NO_COLOR
Disables colored output when set.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "~/.gale/config.toml" -compact
.It Pa ~/.gale/gale.toml
Global package declarations.
.It Pa ~/.gale/config.toml
Application settings.
.It Pa ~/.gale/pkg/
Package store.
.It Pa ~/.gale/current/
Active generation symlink.
.It Pa gale.toml
Project package declarations.
.It Pa gale.lock
Lockfile.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr direnv 1
